race.comment: Tough finish to the day. PEPERONCINO (2) doesn't win out of turn but looks to have come back well. Fresh-up settled off the pace, loomed up and almost got there before peaking on run. Fitter and drawn for a good run here in a high-pressure contest. Repeat would see him go close. A few of these come through a race at Morphettville behind Heaven Rocks. WHOOPS A DAISY (12) was in that same race and sat up on speed before fading late. Did also run well here two back. Wins are rare but seems to be going along pretty well for a race like this. LAPILLI (9) is a former Jolly galloper now in a new barn. Hasn't trialled publicly but does go very well fresh. Watch the betting closely. SABERMETRIC (4) was a close-up fifth latest and is a third-up winner. Looks ready to fire.
